    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Return digest of msg for given secret key and digest. The function is equivalent to HMAC(key, msg, digest).digest(), but uses an optimized C or inline implementation, which is faster for messages that fit into memory. The parameters key, msg, and digest have the same meaning as in new(). CPython implementation detail, the optimized C implementation is only used when digest is a string and name of a digest algorithm, which is supported by OpenSSL. Added in version 3.7."
